      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "How this works",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Single-pass outfit + character draw (FLUX.2)\n\nOne generation that takes **1 clothing reference + 3 character face references** (FLUX.2 supports up to 10) via chained ReferenceLatent -> FluxKontextMultiReferenceLatentMethod('index').\n\n- **Ref 1 = clothing** (best: garment isolated / ghost-mannequin, neutral background, full view).\n- **Refs 2-4 = character faces** (use varied expressions/angles, clean backgrounds).\n- FLUX.2 synthesizes the body, drapes the garment, and applies the face identity, directed by the prompt.\n- Fewer than 3 faces? Bypass (Ctrl-B) the unused LoadImage+VAEEncode+ReferenceLatent for that slot.\n\nNote: in a 1024x2048 full-body frame the face is small, so identity is softer than the dedicated high-res face-refine stage in vn_outfit_reference_draw_then_face_refine_flux2.json. Use that two-stage file if you need maximum face fidelity."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
